Simply snap a picture of any printed offer, and SnipSnap magically converts all the text, images and barcodes into a mobile-optimized offer, which you can redeem off your screen. <\/p><br \/>\n<p>Gather up all the coupons you have lying around. Whether they're from the Sunday paper, the mail, or just ones you found buried in your purse or couch, SnipSnap will mobilize them in a matter of minutes. When you get to a store, pull up the coupon barcode, promo code, or photograph and present to the cashier to redeem. <\/p><br \/>\n<p>Don't have any coupons handy to scan? Use the Discover screen of the app to see what coupons your friends and family have snipped. You can also snip from or follow our featured coupon bundles, and search our massive database of coupons to find one on demand. Best of all: We'll remind you when you enter a store you have coupons saved for, or when a coupon expiration date is nearing. Aw, snap!<\/p><br \/>\n<p>FEATURES:<br>\u2022 IN-STORE REMINDERS: When you enter a store, SnipSnap delivers a push notification to remind you what coupons you have saved there.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>\u2022 SCANS ALL COUPONS: Whether you get coupons from the newspaper, mail, magazines or elsewhere, you can import all of them into the app.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>\u2022 FOLLOW FRIENDS: Connect to friends from your address book, Facebook, or Twitter accounts. Option to share your couponing activity to Facebook.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>\u2022 EXPIRATION DATE ALERTS: Get notified when your coupons' expiration dates are approaching.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>\u2022 STORE SUCCESS RATING: See how successful other users have been in redeeming at your favorite stores.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>***<br>REVIEWS:<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Before you buy anything online or off, search first to see if there's coupons for it. This feature uses a method for reporting location changes in the background. Note that this is only invoked and reported upon a significant location change event -- e.g. moving between two cell towers. As a result it does not typically cause the battery to be drained (unless you are, say, driving all day in the car). Location reporting can be easily disabled via the \"Location Notifications\" toggle in the Settings screen.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>** Works at most retail, restaurant and local businesses. Simply snap a picture of any printed offer, and SnipSnap magically converts all the text, images and barcodes into a mobile-optimized offer, which you can redeem off your screen. \nGather up all the coupons you have lying around. Whether they're from the Sunday paper, the mail, or just ones you found buried in your purse or couch, SnipSnap will mobilize them in a matter of minutes. When you get to a store, pull up the coupon barcode, promo code, or photograph and present to the cashier to redeem. \nDon't have any coupons handy to scan? Use the Discover screen of the app to see what coupons your friends and family have snipped. You can also snip from or follow our featured coupon bundles, and search our massive database of coupons to find one on demand. Best of all: We'll remind you when you enter a store you have coupons saved for, or when a coupon expiration date is nearing. Aw, snap!\nFEATURES:\u2022 IN-STORE REMINDERS: When you enter a store, SnipSnap delivers a push notification to remind you what coupons you have saved there.\n\u2022 SCANS ALL COUPONS: Whether you get coupons from the newspaper, mail, magazines or elsewhere, you can import all of them into the app.\n\u2022 FOLLOW FRIENDS: Connect to friends from your address book, Facebook, or Twitter accounts. This feature uses a method for reporting location changes in the background. Note that this is only invoked and reported upon a significant location change event -- e.g. moving between two cell towers. As a result it does not typically cause the battery to be drained (unless you are, say, driving all day in the car). Location reporting can be easily disabled via the \"Location Notifications\" toggle in the Settings screen.\n** Works at most retail, restaurant and local businesses. After scanning barcodes you find on products, for example, you can discover prices and reviews for it. Or, when scanning newer two-dimensional barcodes, like QR Codes, you can access contact information, bookmarks, web site links and more inside.<p>Barcode Scanner+ is an enhanced version of the popular, free Barcode Scanner application, which is a product of the ZXing open-source barcode scanning library from Google. Barcode Scanner+ is based on the same code, and has been developed by one of the two primary authors of the original Barcode Scanner, Sean Owen.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Barcode Scanner+ includes all of Barcode Scanner's functionality, and is intended as a drop-in replacement for Barcode Scanner. It adds several enhancements:<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Better barcode scanning<\/p><br \/>\n<p>- New image processing algorithm for detection of 1D barcode formats, including UPC and EAN product codes<br>- Uses both cores of dual-core processors<br>- Optionally, scan for Aztec and PDF417 barcodes (note: PDF417 support is 'alpha' quality)<br>- Rewritten to take advantage of Java 6, Android 2.2+ APIs, and latest Android SDK features<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Refined user interface<\/p><br \/>\n<p>- Now scan in tall \"portrait\" orientation, in addition to \"landscape\" orientation<br>- More intuitive pattern-based scanning guide<br>- Streamlined and improved user interface elements<br>- Android 4 and tablet device support<br>- Expanded Help screens<\/p><br \/>\n<p>New features<\/p><br \/>\n<p>- Decode a barcode from an image file<br>- Option to scan light-on-dark barcodes<br>- Activate device's LED light to scan in low light<br>- Basic support for scanning NFC tags<br>- Amazon product information<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Also available in \"simple\" version, without functionality that requires special permission. See \"Barcode Scanner+ Simple\".<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Purchasing this application also supports development of the ZXing open-source barcode scanning library.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Barcode Scanner+ does not collect, store or transmit information about its users, nor usage of the application. The application accesses personal information such as contacts and bookmarks only in order to implement application functionality, such as sharing contacts and bookmarks by QR Codes on screen.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>(aka Barcode Scanner Plus)<\/p><br \/>\n<\/div>  <div class=\"show-more-end\"><\/div> ","text_plain_app_description":" Barcode Scanner+, from Sean Owen of ZXing Team, uses the camera on your device to read barcodes of all kinds. The more you use it the better it gets.<p>** Note to existing users, if you are having trouble opening lists, please Sign out of your Sync account and Sign back in. **<\/p><br \/>\n<p>=================== <br>Why you need this app: <br>=================== <\/p><br \/>\n<p>\u2605 Grocery King will save you time, money and effort every time you go out for shopping. <br>\u2605 1000's of everyday shopping items built-in with photos, just tap tap tap to add items to your lists.<br>\u2605 Highly flexible interface &amp; design to cater to basic as well as power users. Easily make it your own.<br>\u2605 Share, sync and email lists easily with friends and family instantly for coordinated shopping.<br>\u2605 Save money by keeping track of items in your pantry\/storage. Get reminder alerts before items expiry.<br>\u2605 Store your loyalty cards, coupons, gift cards within the app. Leave those pesky cards at home.<br>\u2605 Never forgets your shopping history, save your store receipt and barcode within the app for easy lookup later.<br>\u2605 Know exactly when a store is open, get alerted when you are nearby a store, get driving directions or call your store with one click.<br>\u2605 Sync for life, NO subscription fees to pay yearly.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>=========== <br>Top features:<br>=========== <\/p><br \/>\n<p>\u2714 Create quick shopping lists with option to link to a local retailer. Get retailer store hours, address and phone numbers for 1000's of local retailers near you. Quickly know if a store is open or closed just by glancing at the home screen. <br>\u2714 Create Lists with Location Alerts. Grocery king will now alert you if you happen to pass by a retailer on your way. Smart algorithm will only alert you if the shop is currently open or your have pending items on your shopping list.<br>\u2714 Sort your lists by distance from the retailer to quickly plan your shopping even before stepping out.<br>\u2714 Inventory\/Pantry Manager. Keep track of what stock you already have at home and setup expiry alerts.<br>\u2714 Adding items to shopping lists is now simpler than ever. The new quick search not only allows you to speak or type an item and select from a bunch of matches but also to quickly edit the item without ever leaving the search box.<br>\u2714 Brand new checkout system that offers you an experience similar to how you would checkout from your retailer\/store. Items, prices, discount, tax and total price are all pre-calculated and shown clearly. You can also attach a photo\/barcode of a real receipt to look it up later.<br>\u2714 New History view stores all your previous shopping history sorted by shopping date along with your receipt and barcode.<br>\u2714 Quick and easy way to attach real item photos to an item, never get the wrong item again. <br>\u2714 Unit Price comparison. Now you can compare unit prices between stores so that you know exactly who is selling it cheaper. <br>\u2714 All new way to store your Store Loyalty cards, Retailer coupons &amp; Gift cards. Receive alert notification before the cards expire. <br>\u2714 Brand new recipe view. Easily create and catalog all your recipes and their ingredients. Make buying on eBay fun again!<p>Snipe to win on eBay.<br>Myibidder Bid Sniper is a sniper for eBay buyers that places the last seconds bids to increase your chances to win.<br>No need to watch for auctions anymore, just set a snipe and let the sniper do the job for you.<br>Once the snipe is set, you don't need to keep the app running for the snipe to work.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>The Pro version adds Groups support (set a bunch of items for sniping in the same Group, set limit how many to win. The sniper will stop automatically after it reached your limit).<br>You have to enable Groups in Preferences (open the menu on \"Main Menu\" screen, click \"Preferences\", check \"My Groups\").<br>It also adds \"Current bid\" field. This is not a real-time update, this is the current bid of the last manual Refresh of the listing.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Here is a nice review by guys at Which App.tv:<br><a href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v%3DrCUjH1mBIZA&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNHNaNdpp2RKNOtM3yCGQDy70cLxdA\" target=\"_blank\">http:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=rCUjH1mBIZA<\/a><\/p><br \/>\n<p>Step by step instructions on how to add an item for sniping:<br><a href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/www.myibidder.com\/forums\/viewtopic\/3719\/howto-how-to-add-a-snipe-to-android-app\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGwZZlOOJokJf4M42jNQITg5hqNDg\" target=\"_blank\">http:\/\/www.myibidder.com\/forums\/viewtopic\/3719\/howto-how-to-add-a-snipe-to-android-app\/<\/a><\/p><br \/>\n<p>========================================================<br>For those who never used eBay sniper in the past:<br>1. SNIPING DOES NOT GUARANTEE WINNING. YOU HAVE TO MEET EBAY'S AND SELLER'S REQUIREMENTS IN ORDER TO WIN.<br>ALSO, YOUR SNIPE MUST BE READY (ADDED &amp; ACTIVATED) AT LEAST 3 MINUTES IN ADVANCE.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>2. YOUR SNIPING LIST IS DIFFERENT FROM ITEMS YOU PLACED YOUR BIDS ALREADY.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>3. YOU CAN STOP SNIPING IF YOU HAVE AT LEAST 1-2 MINUTES TO GO BY SETTING \"OFF\" ON \"Activate Snipe\" AND SAVING YOUR CHANGES.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>4. GROUPED ITEMS MUST BE AT LEAST 1 minute APART FROM EACH OTHER, OR YOU MAY WIN THEM ALL.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>5. IT'S ALSO TECHNICALLY NOT POSSIBLE TO SHOW THE CURRENT PRICE IN REAL-TIME IN THE APP. THE \"CURRENT BID\" IS THE BID SINCE YOUR LAST REFRESH.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Questions? Want to get answers? Please feel free to ask:<br><a href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/www.myibidder.com\/forums\/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNHKDoTEl1Dt82GGfnIkYPMIcO7OoA\" target=\"_blank\">http:\/\/www.myibidder.com\/forums\/<\/a><br>Android Market is not for questions or suggestions. We have no way to contact you back and answer you through feedbacks.<br>========================================================<\/p><br \/>\n<p>CURRENT LIMITATIONS:<br>a. Does not refresh information automatically so if you miss snipe status, you have to do \"Refresh\" from the My Main Menu<\/p><br \/>\n<p>The application uses Myibidder.com service (originally named Myibay.com) to place your snipes, so you can turn off or disconnect your phone after you scheduled your snipe.<br>Currently, the service processes over 150,000 snipes weekly.<br>Sniping is done using eBay US by default.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>The Myibidder.com service is completely free. No monthly fees, no per-auction fees, nothing.<br>The service is supported by donations of our users (such as purchasing this application):<br><a href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/www.myibidder.com\/login\/donate&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGpLVKjXpeNEBOgAh_u1HTj64RVkQ\" target=\"_blank\">http:\/\/www.myibidder.com\/login\/donate<\/a><\/p><br \/>\n<p>This application is in Beta stage, it's a proof of concept and testing user interface design. However, it's capable of placing real snipes on real eBay listings.<br>There are few bugs here and there, but it should not affect sniping.<br>Make sure you have at least 3-4 minutes before auction ends when scheduling your snipe.<br>Security tokens has very limited support. It's recommended not to use it when sniping. Please contact support for more details.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>By using Myibidder.com service you have to agree to the following terms:<br><a href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/www.myibidder.com\/login\/terms&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNE1m1rEscunWPF_zutc8wbqigb3AA\" target=\"_blank\">http:\/\/www.myibidder.com\/login\/terms<\/a><\/p><br \/>\n<p>The comments on Android Market are NOT for bug reports and suggestions. Make a quick grocery list, and track your spend while you shop so that you don't exceed your pre-set budget. Multiple ways to generate shopping lists, including barcodes, voice input, free type text and item pickers. Generate a realistic shopping bill at any time complete with taxes and discounts both at item level and overall level. Save multiple shopping lists and send\/export the lists in various formats. It supports multiple currencies and is a useful companion for travel.<br>.<br>This is the Pro version of the popular free utility \"Shop Calc: Budget Grocery List\". It supports all the features of the free version. In addition, the following features are present:<br>.<br>- Ad-free, no ads (more screen space)<br>- Requires no device permissions<br>- Unlimited saved lists (item pickers)<br>- Barcode support (please see notes below)<br>- Voice Input (please see notes below)<br>- 4 row keyboard similar to calculator\/phone<br>.<br>Store the commonly shopped grocery and other items under categorised lists. Even if you are too busy to do that, don't worry, it will build a database of the  products that you shop along with the most recent price and associated tax. Apart from unlimited lists, the pro version also has support for barcodes and voice input.<br>.<br>A quick list entry mode allows you to free type your shopping list quickly. Numerous settings are provided in the Settings screen to customise the behavior to your individual and regional preferences. You can export your shopping list to various formats, mail it or send it via bluetooth.<br>.<br>It is lightweight, requires absolutely no permissions and can be moved to SD card. You have to try it out to see how handy it is. <br>.<br>IMPORTANT NOTES:<br>.<br>Barcode Support: It supports item entry using product barcodes on devices with camera and barcode scanning software. You need to have Google Goggles or ZXing Barcode Scanner software present in your device. The ZXing Barcode Scanner seems to be better at this time. Please note that the item names or price are not fetched. However, if you enter the name, price and tax once, it is remembered for the next time you buy the same product. A lookup is provided to search for the scanned barcode on the net.<br>.<br>Voice Input: Inputing items by voice is possible if the relevant hardware (mic) and software support (Google Voice Search) is available. The voice detection is dependent on your accent and is subject to your phones hardware and software capability.<br>.<br>Shop Calc can be very flexible. It can be used as an adder for counting, for keeping track of  game scores, for calculating the total sales price of items you want to sell, for repeated measuring, for mathematics games etc. In fact, be a little creative, and you can use it for anything where you want to track a series of numbers (continuous addition) with or without a description or remark attached! This simple adder can be used when you want to, say, keep adding and logging how much of each item type is there. When you are taking measurements of your room, why not log it in Shop Calc?<br>.<br>Shop Calc supports Emoji (Emoticons) in Jelly Bean, KitKat and above. Use the smiley button in your Android keyboard to associate some nice icons with your product names.<br>.<br>Instructional Video:<br><a href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v%3Dxm8YGEfA-ck&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNFmXc88JRNIIHbJfRubPbzIViaYVA\" target=\"_blank\">http:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=xm8YGEfA-ck<\/a><br>.<br>Multi-lingual Help:<br><a href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?q=http:\/\/www.panagola.com\/shopcalcpro_v4_help.html&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGDWu4hzdkIJpaqV8ewP40XlY95Mg\" target=\"_blank\">http:\/\/www.panagola.com\/shopcalcpro_v4_help.html<\/a><br>.<br>.<br>Note: This app features a scalable HD design with support for LG Nexus 4, Google Nexus 7 &amp; 10, Galaxy S3 &amp; S4, Galaxy Note 2 &amp; 3, Galaxy Tab 3, HTC One, Sony Xperia Z and various other High Definition Tegra, Exynos and Snapdragon devices and tablets. How do you easily do price comparison?<p>That's a thing of the past.  With Simple Pricebook, you simply enter the price and it will show you comparisons in a simple manner.  No \"unit prices\".  You don't care if this item costs 7.3\u00a2\/oz and this one is 9.2\u00a2\/oz.  Sure, that tells you what's cheaper, but how much are you really saving?  If you're buying 10 oz, then you have a savings of 19\u00a2.  If you're buying 5 lbs, you have a savings of $1.52. <\/p><br \/>\n<p>Simple Pricebook will take all of your comparisons and put them in perspective of the quantity you're looking at.  So if I'm looking at 2 liters of soda, it will compare against that 144 fl oz of soda (12 pack of cans), in a \"2 liter\" manner.  It will tell me the total price of the comparison and the difference.  The difference is color-coded.  Green means it's cheaper and red means it's more expensive.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Want to just see the prices of items? So you will never forget to buy something!<p>BuyNote User Guide<\/p><br \/>\n<p>\uff0aInitial Window\uff0a<br>The initial window is the calendar. A button of number 7 of the right-corner of the calendar is to switch the display from monthly to weekly.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>\uff0aButtons of the calendar (from the left)\uff0a<br>1) Add button: Select the date and tap this button to move to \"Enter List\" window.<br>2) Today button: Go back to today's date.<br>3) Left&amp;Right button: Move the date right to left.<br>4) List button: You can see the list of saved items.<br>\u30fc\u30fc\u30fc\u30fcShopping bucket button of the list\u30fc\u30fc\u30fc\u30fc<br>You can make a new shopping list by tapping each shopping bucket. <br>\u30fc\u30fc\u30fc\u30fcMenu button of the list\u30fc\u30fc\u30fc\u30fc<br>When you see the list, press menu button then press Search. The list of saved items will be displayed. Tap an item you want to add to the list.<br>c) Memo: Take a memo.<br>d) Select quantity from categories: Instead of typing the number, you can select quantities from those list. You can customize your own categories as well. Plus button is Add button. You can create a new category. Pencil button is Edit button. Edit the category and make a new.<br>e): Quantity: Press this button to type the number of the item.<br>f) Delete button: Delete the item.<br>g)Add button (bottom of the window): Save the item and continue to make a list without moving the window! <br>h)  Back button: Go back to the calendar.<\/p><br \/>\n<p>\uff0aWhen you go shopping\uff0a<br>You can see the saved items in the list of the calendar window. You have the option to save the blocked text messages so you can read them after you \u201cunblock\u201d the contact. Or we can discard the text messages as they come in. You can still send text messages to the contact while they are blocked. We have added the \u201cCall Blocker\u201d feature for that contact that is really a pain. (UA Bureau of Applied Research in Anthropology). Not only that, it has serious environmental implications too!<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Best Before is an application designed to track when your food goes off and to alert you before this happens so you can use it before it's too late. Using your smartphone's camera it is possible to scan the barcode of a product and add it to a list of food you have. Keep track of what's in your fridge, cupboard or anywhere else!<\/p><br \/>\n<p>Features:<br># Automatic food name discovery<br># Automatic food expiration discovery<br># Calculates the average number of days before the item will expire.<br># Customise what time to be alerted.<br># Customise how many days before the food expires to be alerted.<br># Customisable automatic expired food removal if a certain amount of days expired.<br># Turn off notifications globally or per item<\/p><br \/>\n<p>I designed this application as I am a student and have very little money to waste. (UA Bureau of Applied Research in Anthropology). Not only that, it has serious environmental implications too!\nBest Before is an application designed to track when your food goes off and to alert you before this happens so you can use it before it's too late.
